Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.98,0:00:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.77,0:00:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.98,0:00:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up, Waver Velvet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.82,0:00:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Kayneth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.70,0:00:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.91,0:00:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, are my lectures too ridiculous for you to listen to?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.71,0:00:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not exactly the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.83,0:00:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, answer me this!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.79,0:00:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you seek to enter the Fifth Holy Grail War?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.67,0:00:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you seek with the relic you stole from me in hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.30,0:00:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and what do you desire?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.26,0:00:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,want to see him one more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.98,0:00:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.35,0:00:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Servants are nothing more than familiars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.85,0:00:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time they materialize, someone like you won't be remembered at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.69,0:00:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Even then... Even then, I want to prove to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.66,0:00:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was the one who was inferior.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.24,0:01:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That he...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.66,0:01:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Rider was the hero who should've been victorious!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.96,0:01:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still think that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.00,0:01:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Relic has been seized.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.92,0:01:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hephaestion, who materialized, denied you as a subject of the King of Conquerors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.43,0:01:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even then, you say you'll still fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.01,0:01:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.01,0:01:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer me once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.81,0:01:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think victory is for a magus?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.89,0:01:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Being rid of all stereotypes and simply arriving at the final destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.77,0:01:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what is your final destination?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.69,0:01:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer me, Lord El-Melloi II!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.57,0:01:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I will answer you, my mentor!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.37,0:01:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What I need to seek right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.04,0:01:46.09,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{OP}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.43,0:03:15.47,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Episode}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.64,0:03:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.05,0:03:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,did you save me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.97,0:03:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You were a warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.94,0:03:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Warriors should die on battlefields whenever possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you'll kill if it comes to battle again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.65,0:03:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You are somehow similar to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell when I look at that weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.74,0:03:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be a replica of a\NNoble Phantasm of some great hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.92,0:03:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, the wielder, also are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:03:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A living incarnation of a distant ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A counterfeit created for show.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.13,0:04:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans never change no matter what era.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.85,0:04:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,However, though counterfeit,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you fight with your own desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.69,0:04:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.77,0:04:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My desires...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.86,0:04:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.16,0:04:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't fight like that without any desires for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My current desire is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.41,0:04:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.62,0:04:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You despise that narrow-minded scholar to come out into the battlefield that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.51,0:04:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed. He will die if he enters a Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.30,0:04:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not of a caliber to be victorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.55,0:04:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is what he desires!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to grant him that wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Loyalty and glory sometimes are contradictory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.19,0:05:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you can't overcome that contradiction, both Master and Servant will perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.32,0:05:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Master and Servant...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.03,0:05:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A king is like the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.20,0:05:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Its heat burns away anything that gets near.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.62,0:05:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But subjects can't survive without the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.50,0:05:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For you, was Iskandar, King of Conquerors,\Nsomeone of that nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.50,0:05:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be no other king like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he falls to illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.63,0:05:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he said he was going to go further and see the Sea at the End of the World.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.22,0:05:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A grand king drove us forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How heated all of his words were...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How much they glimmered...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.15,0:05:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was his primary confidante.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.78,0:05:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something I won't let anyone deny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But why were you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.12,0:05:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were you alone reprimanding Iskandar for his actions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.96,0:05:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Hephaestion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.96,0:05:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.67,0:06:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer me! What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.17,0:06:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you were asking,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.22,0:06:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"Is this what you desired?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.14,0:06:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why didn't you let this go?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.72,0:06:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You said, "Answer me, Iskandar!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.90,0:06:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I should've known.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.57,0:06:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a Sibyl. It seems you're especially versed in spiritual possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.03,0:06:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it stopped snowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When you can move again, you can leave here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Though I don't know if you can catch up to that train.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Mary Lil Fargo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.55,0:06:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you talk to us about Trisha Fellows?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.22,0:06:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She's an old friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.02,0:07:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, she has passed away. I still can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.48,0:07:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She was investigating a serial murder that happened seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.77,0:07:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard anything about why she did so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.78,0:07:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Olga Marie was abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.12,0:07:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Trisha said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Olga Marie is, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.70,0:07:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the daughter of Lord Animusphere!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.41,0:07:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about a month ago. The last day that I met her...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven years ago, Lord Animusphere was researching about the Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.13,0:07:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Holy Grail War?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.80,0:07:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It was right around when the serial murders were happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.22,0:07:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lord gained information about the Holy Grail War from somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.64,0:07:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's a very minor magecraft ritual in the Far East, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.85,0:07:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you look into it after all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Since doing research about the Holy Grail War,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.57,0:07:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,after a while, the Lord stopped showing interest in Olga Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But a magus not leaving anything for his child can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.12,0:07:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That Greater Grail was distorted,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:08:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and no matter what you do, it can't grant the family's wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.91,0:08:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the Lord said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.50,0:08:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But what does that have to do with him abandoning his daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the Lord find out seven years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.67,0:08:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it related to the serial murder case?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.59,0:08:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And why did he abandon Olga Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Trisha was doing research on the Holy Grail War,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.81,0:08:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and she boarded the Mystic Eyes Collection Train.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The victims of the serial murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.94,0:08:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,including Trisha herself, were wielders of Mystic Eyes. Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.11,0:08:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A man without a heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.82,0:08:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone with a nickname like that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.07,0:08:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was doing research on the Holy Grail War\Nseven years ago by request from Lord Animusphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.25,0:08:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.04,0:08:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.50,0:08:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This was of great help to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.72,0:08:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing less from the Rail Zeppelin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.63,0:09:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If it can locate a leyline, not even the Child of Ainnash will be an obstacle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.81,0:09:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a time to be celebrating?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.31,0:09:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I really do feel sorry about Gray!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, she seems like she can take a few hits!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.61,0:09:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough with the excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.28,0:09:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.53,0:09:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That hurts! It's cold!\NI'm being shaven, planed, grated!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.79,0:09:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, ouch, pain, ouch, pain,\NI'm shaven, planed, grated, pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Open the door please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.64,0:09:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And there we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.68,0:09:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Made it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.31,0:09:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.56,0:09:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is so amusing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.39,0:09:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It definitely was worth crashing a helicopter for!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Caules, how is Master doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.48,0:09:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.98,0:09:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,His condition stabilized soon after leaving that forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.99,0:09:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What, weak in the knees?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.07,0:10:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And harsh treatment aside, you didn't have to ride on the shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.99,0:10:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.41,0:10:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be more mannered in how you treat a box—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.21,0:10:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Gray! Stop! Hey! Stop! Gray! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.42,0:10:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's wrong, Missie?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.17,0:10:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You suddenly have a sour look on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A man without a heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.68,0:10:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard rumors of a dangerous magus who once had his heart stolen by a Fairy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,By a Fairy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.68,0:10:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's the person I know of, he has a younger sister-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.35,0:10:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's currently aboard that train.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.73,0:10:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.23,0:10:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.11,0:10:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm having everyone gather up in the lobby car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the usual individual is still sleeping slovenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I will play detective for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.34,0:10:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world is the reason you want all of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.34,0:11:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something I'd like to suggest from the standpoint of the Policies division.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it's about the perpetrator of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.64,0:11:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, Great Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.02,0:11:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a serial murder case that used the same method seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.69,0:11:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me, but I don't recollect any cases of that nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.45,0:11:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We at Policies had controlled information about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.03,0:11:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you'd actually admit that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.33,0:11:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we weren't the only ones who meddled in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.12,0:11:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Holy Church had also intervened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.46,0:11:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The investigator in charge at the time was you, Karabo Frampton, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.88,0:11:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on now! If you knew about it, you could say so!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.68,0:11:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That goes against my duties of confidentiality. Naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.10,0:11:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with Mr. Karabo's Past Vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.23,0:11:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the crime scene couldn't be viewed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.69,0:11:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with Miss Trisha's Premonition, she couldn't protect her own self.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.23,0:11:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.73,0:12:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the instant of the crime couldn't be viewed either from the past or the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.66,0:12:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That would leave us with one answer, plain and simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That location wasn't the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.66,0:12:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! I get it! But of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.75,0:12:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As I'd expect from a Mystic Eyes specialist...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.21,0:12:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Past Vision and Premonition only transcend over the temporal axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, if you're not at the scene of the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.59,0:12:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't see visions no matter how hard you try.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The crime scene wasn't that room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, who are you saying murdered Miss Trisha?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.02,0:12:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'll have one witness enter the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.95,0:12:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.29,0:12:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Her head was hidden using Imaginary Numbers Magecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.00,0:13:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I presume that Trisha Fellows herself had sealed it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.13,0:13:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She sealed away her own head?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She likely realized she was going to die by beheading thanks to her Premonition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.89,0:13:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd created an Imaginary pocket in advance to where the head would likely fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.60,0:13:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.10,0:13:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside a spell of Imaginary Numbers Magecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,time stands still.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.52,0:13:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, her head at the time of retrieval was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.99,0:13:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It was still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.03,0:13:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,With the final breath left in her throat, she uttered just one word.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.04,0:13:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think was the word she left behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.71,0:13:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"Karabo."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.05,0:13:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Karabo Frampton,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,your Mystic Eyes are those of Observation of Past Vision, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What is Observation of Past Vision?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.30,0:13:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They're Mystic Eyes that can see a commonplace past.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.14,0:13:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can perceive a past that's already been settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.93,0:13:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you can see the past, you can't commit a murder, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.27,0:14:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.61,0:14:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Among powerful Mystic Eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.69,0:14:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,there are those who can bring the visions into the world as truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, "The Mystic Eyes of Death Perception."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.62,0:14:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The legendary?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.99,0:14:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are Rainbow-class or Jewel-class!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.41,0:14:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, this is only if the rumors are true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.08,0:14:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But your Mystic Eyes are rather close to that, aren't they, Father Karabo?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I will record a slash like this and put it aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.64,0:14:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, if the wielder of the Mystic Eyes had observed it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.18,0:14:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the target will be severed in the exact manner of the recorded slash.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.32,0:14:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.82,0:14:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, didn't you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you do it, Karabo Frampton?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.49,0:14:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A train following the rails worked in your favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.04,0:15:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You just took a slice of empty air in the lobby car leading the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.30,0:15:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be easy to see what location the chair would be with your Past Vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.63,0:15:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when her corpse was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.68,0:15:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the train had stopped in the woods, and you were outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.56,0:15:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You simply needed to peek into the window from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.65,0:15:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, dragged into the past you observed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.98,0:15:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,empty air would be torn apart once again...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.49,0:15:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,right along with Trisha Fellows' head.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.37,0:15:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait? Does that mean the serial murder from seven years ago was also like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.87,0:15:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think there would be anyone else with Mystic Eyes like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.54,0:15:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that individual was involved in the investigation, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.50,0:15:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.13,0:15:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't conclude that you're the perpetrator,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.51,0:15:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but this gives enough reason to take certain measures against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.31,0:15:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:15:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.43,0:16:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you finally awake, Lord El-Melloi II?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.36,0:16:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Waver!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think you'd be here, as well, Melvin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! It's only natural for me to rush over when my best friend's in peril!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Just mind your own business.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Adashino...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.28,0:16:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I have several doubts on your deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already going to let me in on your marvelous detective work?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.50,0:16:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The deduction you just mentioned is lacking the element of motive to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Whydunit, your favorite?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.05,0:16:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct. There is no crime without motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.80,0:16:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really need a reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.81,0:16:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,how about envisioning you and the bloodthirsty killer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.39,0:16:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as one and the same with Mystic Eyes of Past Vision?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.98,0:16:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As he kept observing the murders seven years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.48,0:16:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of self and the killer melded together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that be possible if he no longer can control his Mystic Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you seriously saying that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.86,0:16:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be okay if I was serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.62,0:16:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't much of a difference between serious and nonsensical.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.70,0:17:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, we are magi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.16,0:17:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's your scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But does Father Karabo's Mystic Eyes\N really have that kind of power?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.00,0:17:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.71,0:17:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Who proved that his Mystic Eyes could bring forth a recorded vision of the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.14,0:17:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that is nothing more than my deduction?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even worth calling it a presumption or even circumstantial evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.64,0:17:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To be blunt, it's just a delusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.77,0:17:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to prosecute him based on something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.19,0:17:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to worry about that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.86,0:17:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All we need to do is to have the Mystic Eyes\Nappraised by Rail Zeppelin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It would be possible with those Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.12,0:17:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, it can project a slash lost in the past back into the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, this is the deputy manager of this train.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It is now the appointed time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.13,0:17:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here to take your Mystic Eyes before the auction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:17:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Appointed time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.18,0:18:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The staff should've told you already...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.10,0:18:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that we'll be extracting your Mystic Eyes\Nhalf a day before the auction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.94,0:18:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, so you thought this would be the perfect timing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.44,0:18:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for Rail Zeppelin to back up your deductions!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.28,0:18:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You are perceptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.82,0:18:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.53,0:18:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Deputy Manager...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.80,0:18:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is marvelous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.64,0:18:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls short of Rainbow-class, but it'll likely reach at least Jewel-class.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, it really does?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A past shadow long gone can be brought back to the present like sea-foam.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.69,0:18:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we name it "Mystic Eyes of Transience"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.03,0:19:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I do apologize wholeheartedly for taking all of your precious time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.41,0:19:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you'll be able to resume a pleasant journey aboard Rail Zeppelin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.97,0:19:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, why are you tagging along?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.39,0:19:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I'd tag along! I'm your best friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.35,0:19:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll cry if you keep being so cold to me! I'll cough blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.23,0:19:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think Mr. Karabo was the one who killed Miss Trisha?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.73,0:19:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a large difference between possibility and actual execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry. We're keeping you restrained for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.79,0:19:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.46,0:19:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you really involved in a serial murder seven years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.67,0:19:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.09,0:20:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I honestly had forgotten until just moments ago that I was involved in that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The effects of your Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.64,0:20:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's forced on me even if I don't want to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.48,0:20:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether my eyes are open or shut,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.60,0:20:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the images flood in as if laughing at me that my eyelids don't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.82,0:20:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,However, at a greater pace than that, my own memories become shattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.74,0:20:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of Mystic Eyes they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.16,0:20:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you were completely unable to control those Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.66,0:20:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, if I had those Mystic Eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.29,0:20:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had them, I might finally be able to unravel the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.80,0:20:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you can buy the Mystic Eyes\Nback in the auction!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, but it won't be a sum I can make a winning bid for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.85,0:20:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So, you just want to buy it back?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.64,0:20:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Melvin...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.60,0:20:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't guarantee it because I'm sure it'll be the most expensive item this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.40,0:20:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But it might be fun to at least challenge myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.94,0:21:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it's only if it has that much amusement attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.99,0:21:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Waver?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.82,0:21:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intent on selling my soul to the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.12,0:21:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A shame...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.49,0:21:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there something to make this case a bit more exciting?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.87,0:21:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, when I met Miss Trisha...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.71,0:21:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Tucked in her clothes was, well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,something lewd.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.88,0:21:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.84,0:21:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me again! What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.47,0:21:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a man and a woman connected together—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.47,0:21:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not strange to bring something in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.85,0:21:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself had taken several defensive measures.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.94,0:21:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But nothing like that was at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.15,0:21:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it was a defensive measure,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.94,0:21:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it's nowhere nearly as stable as a Mystic Eyes nullifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.57,0:21:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that means she had a different way to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.33,0:21:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.45,0:21:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a deduction.\NI can't possibly call this a deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.41,0:21:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.46,0:21:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,if what I imagine is true, I can say this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.29,0:22:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.50,0:22:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,my enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.59,0:22:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I will solve...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.43,0:22:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.93,0:22:09.98,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{ED}
